EMERGENCY LANDING PROCEDURES
In the unlikely
event that an
emergency landing should become necessary,
listen carefully to all instructions given by the crew.
BRACING POSITION
If the
order is given to assume the bracing
position,
you should do the following:
• Loosen your necktie and collar
• Remove your glasses and dentures
• Remove all sharp objects from your pockets
• Fasten your seat belt securely
• Adopt the braced position as illustrated
SPECIAL INFORMATION FOR OVERWATER FLIGHTS
Should an overwater emergency landing (ditching) become necessary, you should
be aware of certain special procedures:
• There will be two impacts, one when the tail section touches the
water, and another when the wings and main body of the
aircraft touch down
• After the second impact, unfasten your seat belt and make an
orderly evacuation from the aircraft
• You should inflate your life jacket only AFTER you are outside
of the aircraft
LIFE JACKETS AND FLOTATION SEAT CUSHIONS
A placard on the seat in front of you will tell if this aircraft is equipped with LIFE
JACKETS or FLOTATION SEAT CUSHIONS. You should become familiar with the
use of whichever is aboard this aircraft by reading the applicable instructions below:
HOW TO USE A LIFE JACKET
• Remove the Life Jacket from under your seat
• Hold the Life Jacket with the lamp to the front
• Push your head through the neck opening
• Insert waist strap through buckle and pull tight
• Inflate by pulling down sharply on the plastic knob only AFTER
you are outside the aircraft
• If necessary, the Life Jacket may be inflated by blowing into
the mouthpiece provided
• The light may be activated by pulling the plug from the bottom
of the battery. When the sea water contacts the battery, the
light automatically comes on
HOW TO USE A FLOTATION SEAT CUSHION
• Remove the bottom seat cushion from your seat
• Hold the seat cushion directly in front of you
• Place your arms through the loops like putting on a coat backwards
• Lock your hands in front of you to hold cushion to chest
• Do not wear cushion on your back as this will cause you to float
face down
PLEASE DO NOT REMOVE THIS CARD FROM THE AIRCRAFT
